Electrum-Doge - lightweight Dogecoin client

Licence: GNU GPL v3
Electrum Author: Thomas Voegtlin
Electrum-Doge Contributors: Riccardo Spagni, Michael Wozniak
Language: Python
Electrum Homepage: http://electrum.org/

Electrum-Doge Homepage: http://electrum-doge.org/


1. GETTING STARTED
------------------

To run Electrum-Doge from this directory, just do:

  ./electrum-doge

If you install Electrum on your system, you can run it from any
directory:

  sudo python setup.py install

To start Electrum-Doge from your web browser, see
http://electrum-doge.org/bitcoin_URIs.html



2. HOW OFFICIAL PACKAGES ARE CREATED
------------------------------------

python mki18n.py
pyrcc4 icons.qrc -o gui/qt/icons_rc.py
python setup.py sdist --format=zip,gztar

On Mac OS X:

  # On port based installs
  sudo python setup-release.py py2app

  # On brew installs
  ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386 -arch x86_64" sudo python setup-release.py py2app --includes sip

  sudo hdiutil create -fs HFS+ -volname "Electrum-Doge" -srcfolder dist/Electrum-Doge.app dist/electrum-doge-VERSION-macosx.dmg

